@node Guide
@chapter Guide

This guide walks you through @strong{every feature}, in the order you would actually
meet them: install and verify, onboard a client, capture work, read the
dashboard, look across clients, and tailor the system. It assumes you are
comfortable in Emacs and Org (@samp{M-x}, @samp{C-c c} capture, the agenda dispatcher,
editing your init file).

It complements the other two documents rather than repeating them:

@itemize
@item
This @strong{guide} is the hand-held tour — @emph{how do I use the tool?}
@item
@uref{playbook.org, playbook.org} is the methodology — @emph{how do I run the engagement?}
@item
@uref{reference.org, reference.org} is the lookup — @emph{what does each capture and tag mean?}
@end itemize

Work through it once, top to bottom, with Emacs open. Every step says what you
should @strong{see} so you can confirm it worked before moving on.

