@node Step 8 — Read your dashboard
@section Step 8 — Read your dashboard

Press @code{C-c a E} (or @code{M-x org-fractional-cto-dashboard}). You get a @strong{global} board
spanning all client files, with nine blocks, in this order:

@enumerate
@item
@strong{Next 7 days} — scheduled items and deadlines from the hub.
@item
@strong{Delegated — awaiting response} — everything @samp{WAITING}, deadline-sorted.
This is your "work I am owed" inbox; nothing should sit here a full week
without a check-in.
@item
@strong{Blockers & escalations} — anything tagged @samp{BLOCKER}.
@item
@strong{Open actions} — your @samp{TODO} / @samp{NEXT} / @samp{INPROGRESS} work, with blockers and
commitments filtered out so they are not double-listed.
@item
@strong{Commitments} — promises made, by you or the client.
@item
@strong{Active risks} — the risk register (the section container is skipped, so you
see the risks themselves, not the empty parent heading). A risk closed out
with @samp{Status: Resolved} or @samp{Mitigated} drops off the board; @samp{Open} and
@samp{Accepted} risks stay.
@item
@strong{Open security findings} — @samp{[SECURITY]} findings, with closed-out ones
(@samp{Status: Resolved} or @samp{Mitigated}) filtered out — the @strong{same closed-set rule}
as risks.
@item
@strong{Open tech debt} — every @samp{[TECH DEBT]} item recorded for the client.
@item
@strong{Scope changes — pending decisions} — @samp{SCOPE CHANGE} entries sorted by their
"decision needed by" deadline, so a decision due beyond the seven-day agenda
window is still visible here.
@end enumerate

Blocks 6–9 are the @strong{watch list}: severity-rated liabilities (risks, security
findings, tech debt) and scope decisions that carry no @samp{TODO} keyword and so
would otherwise never appear in an action view.

Because the dashboard is a @strong{real Org agenda command}, not a bespoke function, it
inherits the dispatcher's powers: refresh with @samp{r}, filter with @samp{/}, narrow by
tag, export, and it is sticky-agenda aware. The dashboard spans @strong{all} client
files. When an active client is set, the view opens pre-focused on that client
via the native @samp{org-agenda-tag-filter-preset}, and the @samp{CATEGORY} column shows
each entry's client. Use the agenda's native @samp{/} key to widen, refocus on a
different client, or clear the filter; there is no separate focus command.
@samp{org-fractional-cto-set-tag-inheritance} (on by default) ensures the inherited
client filetag is visible to the filter.
@samp{M-x org-fractional-cto-switch-client} sets a different client active and
re-opens the board pre-focused to it in one step.

@node Step 9 — Look across all clients
@section Step 9 — Look across all clients

With an active client the dashboard opens focused; clear the filter (@samp{/} then
@samp{<RET>}) to go portfolio-wide without leaving the board. For raw cross-client
lookups by type, use the plain agenda dispatcher:

@multitable {aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa} {aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa}
@headitem Keys
@tab Shows
@item @code{C-c a m RISK}
@tab Every risk, across all clients
@item @code{C-c a m DELEGATED}
@tab Everything you have delegated, anywhere
@item @code{C-c a m BLOCKER}
@tab All blockers everywhere
@item @code{C-c a t}
@tab All TODOs across clients
@end multitable

The full tag legend (one tag per capture type) is in the README and
@uref{reference.org, reference.org}. The pattern: @samp{C-c a m <TAG>} turns any capture type into a
cross-client list.

