@node Override a single template
@subsection Override a single template

Copy the bundled @samp{templates/} folder somewhere of your own, edit only the file
you care about (say @samp{adr.org}), and point the variable at your copy:

@lisp
(setq org-fractional-cto-template-directory "~/org/ofc-templates")
@end lisp

@node Reorder or extend the dashboard
@subsection Reorder or extend the dashboard

@samp{org-fractional-cto-dashboard-blocks} is an ordinary list of Org agenda series
entries. Drop a block, reorder them, or add your own — for example, a block for
@samp{NEXT} items first — then re-run @code{M-x org-fractional-cto-setup} to apply it (the
install is idempotent, so this refreshes the command in place).

@node Step 12 — Wire in AI session skills (optional)
@section Step 12 — Wire in AI session skills (optional)

If you also do hands-on implementation with an AI agent, two skill packs pair
well with the workflow. They live in your @strong{code} repositories, not here; the
link between them and Org is the @samp{CONTEXT.md} file plus the captured artifacts.
The loop is: Org tells you @emph{what} and @emph{why} → the skill helps you @emph{do} it → you
capture the @emph{outcome} back into Org. See the README's
"Working with AI session skills" section for the per-capture skill mapping.

@node Step 13 — Settle into the rhythm
@section Step 13 — Settle into the rhythm

You now know every moving part. The operating cadence ties them together:

@itemize
@item
@strong{Daily} — attend standups (@samp{es}), capture blockers (@samp{eb}) as they surface.
@item
@strong{Weekly} — delegation + pulse review (@samp{eW}); internal sync (@samp{ei}) before any
client comms; client sync (@samp{em}); sprint retro (@samp{eR}). Clear the @strong{Delegated}
block on the dashboard.
@item
@strong{Monthly} — client health check (@samp{eh}); review the innovation pipeline (@samp{en}).
@item
@strong{Quarterly} — QBR (@samp{eq}); architecture health review (@samp{eA}).
@end itemize

The @emph{why} behind this cadence — the engagement phases, the "hat" model, and the
decision frameworks — is the job of @uref{playbook.org, playbook.org}. Read it next.

@node Troubleshooting
@section Troubleshooting

@itemize
@item
@strong{Every capture prompts me for a client.} No active client is set. Run
@samp{org-fractional-cto-set-active-client} (or @samp{switch-client}). This is expected
behaviour, not a bug — it just means one extra keystroke per capture.

@item
@strong{An @samp{INPROGRESS} task is missing from the dashboard's Open actions.} First
confirm @samp{org-fractional-cto-setup} ran — it registers @samp{INPROGRESS} globally, so
if it never ran (and the file lacks a @samp{#+TODO} line) the state is unknown.
Second, the keyword must be exactly @samp{INPROGRESS}, with @strong{no hyphen}. Org's
agenda match language treats @samp{-} as a boolean NOT, so a hyphenated keyword
(@samp{IN-PROGRESS}) is parsed as "@samp{IN} and not @samp{PROGRESS}" and never matches.
Scaffolded hubs use the hyphen-free form; if you have an old hub, fix its
@samp{#+TODO} line and any task states.

@item
@strong{The dashboard shows no entries for my client.} The dashboard now spans all
client files. If no active client is set, all clients appear unfiltered. Set
one with @samp{M-x org-fractional-cto-set-active-client} to focus the board. If the
filter is not working, ensure @samp{org-fractional-cto-set-tag-inheritance} is @samp{t} (the
default) so the inherited client filetag is visible to the agenda filter.

@item
@strong{A standup capture inserts literal @samp{%^@{...@}} / @samp{%U} text.} You are on an old
version where the standup was injected as a string. Update the package; the
standup is now read as a file template so its escapes expand normally.

@item
@strong{@code{C-c a E} is not listed in the dispatcher.} @samp{setup} has not run (or ran
before Org loaded). Ensure @samp{org-fractional-cto-setup} runs @samp{:after org}, then
re-run it — it is idempotent.

@item
@strong{I changed config but nothing updated.} Re-run @code{M-x org-fractional-cto-setup}.
It refreshes captures and the dashboard in place; no restart needed.
@end itemize

