@node Playbook
@chapter Playbook

A repeatable process for onboarding, running, and growing client engagements as a
Fractional CTO & Engagement Director. Adapt per client — this is a map, not a script.

The playbook operates across five phases. Each phase has a dominant @strong{hat}, a set of
@strong{questions to drive the work}, the @strong{capture templates} to use, and a @strong{deliverable}.

@menu
* The Hat Model::
* Phase −1 — Pre-Sales / Pipeline::
* Phase 0 — Engagement Setup::
* Phase 1 — Discovery::
* Phase 2 — Architecture Assessment::
* Phase 3 — Operating Rhythm::
* Phase 4 — Growth & Innovation::
* New Client Onboarding Checklist::
* Reference All Capture Templates::
@end menu

@node The Hat Model
@section The Hat Model

You operate across six modes. The discipline is to not switch hats mid-session.
Schedule explicit @strong{hat blocks} — a discovery session is discovery only; an
architecture session is architecture only. Mixing them produces mediocre output
in both directions.

@multitable {aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa} {aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa} {aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa}
@headitem Hat
@tab When to wear it
@tab Key discipline
@item Engagement Director
@tab Client calls, QBRs, scope conversations
@tab Speak business outcomes, not tech
@item Discovery
@tab Stream interviews, system mapping
@tab Listen more than you talk
@item Fractional CTO
@tab ADRs, roadmap, build vs. buy decisions
@tab First principles, not vendor bias
@item QA Auditor
@tab Test coverage review, release gates
@tab Find the gaps the team normalised
@item Security Reviewer
@tab Compliance posture, infra review
@tab Assume breach, work backwards
@item DevOps Reviewer
@tab CI/CD, infra, deployment, on-call
@tab Optimise for recovery speed, not uptime
@end multitable

@menu
* Hat-switching tools::
@end menu

@node Hat-switching tools
@subsection Hat-switching tools

@strong{@uref{https://github.com/mattpocock/skills, mattpocock/skills}} — precision tools for focused sessions:
@itemize
@item
@samp{/grill-me} — structured interview @strong{before} any work starts; surfaces misalignment early
@item
@samp{/grill-with-docs} — same, but anchored to a specific document (e.g. an SOW or PRD)
@item
@samp{/zoom-out} — forces system-level thinking before diving into a stream
@item
@samp{/handoff} — compacts the session into a document so context survives a hat switch
@item
@samp{CONTEXT.md} — per-client domain glossary; load it at the start of every Claude Code session
@end itemize

@strong{@uref{https://github.com/garrytan/gstack, garrytan/gstack}} — sprint structure for execution phases:
@itemize
@item
@samp{/office-hours} — six forcing questions that challenge your framing @strong{before} you commit to a direction
@item
@samp{/autoplan} — chains CEO review, engineering review, design review
@item
@samp{/review} — staff-engineer audit after implementation
@item
@samp{/cso} — OWASP Top 10 + STRIDE threat model
@item
@samp{/qa} — real browser QA with regression test generation
@item
@samp{/retro} — weekly retrospective
@end itemize

@strong{Rule:} Run @samp{/office-hours} (gstack) or @samp{/grill-me} (mattpocock) at the @strong{start} of any
non-trivial session. These are your calibration tools. Skip them when you feel rushed.
That's exactly when you need them most.

@node Phase −1 — Pre-Sales / Pipeline
@section Phase −1 — Pre-Sales / Pipeline

@emph{Before the engagement exists. Hat: Trusted Advisor (selling by helping).}

You meet a prospect with almost no information. The goal is to capture
everything you hear, research to fill the gaps, and decide whether to pursue —
without yet committing to the deep, team-by-team discovery of Phase 1.

@itemize
@item
@samp{M-x org-fractional-cto-new-prospect} — create the prospect at @samp{LEAD} stage.
@item
@samp{C-c c el} — capture each pre-sales call: the ask in their words, pain
points, budget/timing signals, decision-makers, and the next step.
@item
@samp{C-c c eo} — log research findings (company, market, competitors, tech hints,
funding, people). Promote durable facts into @samp{CONTEXT.md}.
@item
@samp{C-c c eF} — a fit/qualification scorecard ending in a verdict: Pursue, Hold,
or Pass. On Pursue, note what to validate in the first deep discovery (@samp{ed}).
@end itemize

Advance the stage as conviction grows (@samp{M-x org-fractional-cto-set-stage}:
@samp{LEAD} → @samp{QUALIFIED}), and @samp{C-c a P} is your funnel board across all prospects.
When you win, @samp{set-stage} → @samp{ACTIVE} and proceed to Phase 0 — the hub, its
history, and every captured artifact carry straight over.

