@node Purpose (1)
@subsection Purpose

Build a grounded picture of the system: what exists, who owns it, where the debt
and risk live, and where innovation is possible. Do not skip streams that seem
"boring" (DevOps, QA) — they consistently surface the most critical risks.

@node Rhythm
@subsection Rhythm

One session per stream. After every 2–3 sessions, a 15-minute synthesis pass to
update cross-cutting sections of the master discovery doc before memory fades.

@node Per-session approach
@subsection Per-session approach

@enumerate
@item
Run @samp{/grill-me} or @samp{/zoom-out} (mattpocock/skills) @strong{before} the session to surface
what you're assuming and what you don't know
@item
Use @samp{C-c c ed} (discovery template) to start a clocked session
@item
During the session: listen for what they @strong{don't} say as much as what they do
@item
After the session: refile the capture; update the master doc immediately
@item
After every 2–3 sessions: update cross-cutting sections (security, tech debt, integrations)
@end enumerate

@node Questions that cut across all streams
@subsection Questions that cut across all streams

@itemize
@item
What would break first if load doubled tomorrow?
@item
What's the one thing you'd fix if you had a sprint of uninterrupted time?
@item
What do you not have visibility into that you wish you did?
@item
What's the thing nobody talks about but everyone knows is a problem?
@item
Where are the handoffs between your stream and others rough?
@end itemize

@node Capture templates (1)
@subsection Capture templates

@itemize
@item
@samp{C-c c ed} Discovery session (one per stream)
@item
@samp{C-c c et} Technical debt item (capture as you hear them)
@item
@samp{C-c c ex} Security finding (any compliance or security signal)
@item
@samp{C-c c er} Risk item (any delivery or engagement risk)
@end itemize

@node Deliverable (1)
