@node Purpose (2)
@subsection Purpose

Turn discovery findings into decisions and direction. This is where you earn the
"CTO" part of the title — not by having all the answers, but by asking the right
questions and making the call when teams are stuck.

@node Approach
@subsection Approach

Use @samp{/office-hours} (gstack) before each significant architecture decision to
challenge your own framing. Architecture decisions made under time pressure without
a forcing function tend to optimise for comfort over correctness.

@node Checklist (1)
@subsection Checklist

@itemize
@item
ADR for each significant architectural decision in flight
@item
Technology roadmap draft: what we're building, what we're retiring, and when
@item
Technical debt register: prioritised, owned, with timelines
@item
Compliance posture document: gap analysis for each relevant framework
@item
Build vs. buy positions for all significant components
@item
Engineering standards baseline: what varies across teams that should be standardised
@item
Security posture assessment (run @samp{/cso} from gstack)
@end itemize

@node Build vs Buy decision frame
@subsection Build vs. Buy decision frame

Before recommending build:
@enumerate
@item
Does a commercial solution exist that solves 80%+ of the problem?
@item
What is the total 2-year cost of building vs. buying (including maintenance)?
@item
Is this a differentiating capability or commodity infrastructure?
@item
What is the opportunity cost of the engineering time?
@end enumerate

Before recommending buy:
@enumerate
@item
What is the lock-in exposure if we need to exit?
@item
Does it touch customer data? What are their data handling practices?
@item
Are there contractual terms that could bind the client uncomfortably?
@end enumerate

@node Capture templates (2)
@subsection Capture templates

@itemize
@item
@samp{C-c c ea} ADR — one per significant technology or architecture decision
@item
@samp{C-c c ev} Vendor evaluation — any tool or vendor being assessed
@item
@samp{C-c c et} Technical debt item — from the assessment, not just discovery
@item
@samp{C-c c ex} Security finding — from the compliance posture review
@end itemize

@node Deliverable (2)
@subsection Deliverable

Technology roadmap (quarters, not just quarters). ADR log. Technical debt register
with owners and timelines. Compliance gap analysis with remediation plan.

