@node Purpose (4)
@subsection Purpose

Expand the engagement scope and deepen the relationship through genuine strategic
value — not sales pushes. The best expansions feel like the client's idea.

@node Innovation pipeline approach
@subsection Innovation pipeline approach

@enumerate
@item
Capture opportunities as you discover them (@samp{C-c c en}) — never filter at capture time
@item
Monthly: review the pipeline and select one to develop into a brief
@item
Brief format: business opportunity first, technology second, effort estimate third
@item
Present the best one at each QBR under "Strategic Recommendation"
@item
Frame as: "here's what becomes possible if we@dots{}" not "here's what we could build"
@end enumerate

@node Expansion conversation triggers
@subsection Expansion conversation triggers

@itemize
@item
A stream is hitting a ceiling the client hasn't named yet
@item
You've identified a capability gap across multiple streams
@item
A partner or tool evaluation opens a new product direction
@item
The client asks a question that reveals a problem outside current scope
@end itemize

@node Scope change discipline
@subsection Scope change discipline

Any work identified outside the current SOW must be captured immediately (@samp{C-c c e})
and brought through the internal sync before any client conversation about it.
Never agree to out-of-scope work in a client meeting — "let me come back to you on
what that would look like" is always the right answer in the room.

