@node keywords
@subsection @strong{TODO} keywords

@samp{org-fractional-cto-setup} registers these globally (via @samp{org-todo-keywords}), so
they work in every buffer without touching your personal Org config; client hubs
also declare them locally with @samp{#+TODO: TODO NEXT INPROGRESS WAITING | DONE
CANCELLED}. Customize via @samp{org-fractional-cto-todo-keywords}.

@multitable {aaaaaaaaaaaa} {aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa}
@headitem Keyword
@tab Meaning
@item @samp{TODO}
@tab Open action you own
@item @samp{NEXT}
@tab The next physical action (GTD-style)
@item @samp{INPROGRESS}
@tab Actively being worked
@item @samp{WAITING}
@tab @strong{Delegated} — owned by someone else, you're tracking it
@item @samp{DONE}
@tab Completed
@item @samp{CANCELLED}
@tab Dropped
@end multitable

@samp{WAITING} is load-bearing: it separates "things I owe" from "things I'm owed,"
and feeds the dashboard's @strong{Delegated} block.

@node Engagement stages (tag on the engagement heading)
@subsection Engagement stages (tag on the engagement heading)

One stage tag sits on the top @samp{* … Engagement} heading (e.g. @samp{:ACTIVE:}) and is
inherited by the whole tree. The @strong{client} identity tag (e.g. @samp{:ACME:}) is
declared at the file level via @samp{#+filetags}, not on the engagement heading.
Switch it with @samp{M-x org-fractional-cto-set-stage}.

@multitable {aaaaaaaaaaa} {aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa}
@headitem Stage
@tab Meaning
@item @samp{LEAD}
@tab Captured from a pre-sales call; raw
@item @samp{QUALIFIED}
@tab Researched and worth pursuing (pre-contract)
@item @samp{ACTIVE}
@tab Won / engaged — the default for new-client
@item @samp{LOST}
@tab Did not convert
@item @samp{DORMANT}
@tab Paused / on hold
@end multitable

The pipeline view (@samp{C-c a P}) lists every @samp{LEAD=/=QUALIFIED} engagement across
all clients, one line per prospect.

