@node org-agenda (@samp{C-c a})
@subsection org-agenda (@samp{C-c a})

Your operational dashboard. Key views:

@multitable {aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa} {aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa}
@headitem Key
@tab View
@item @samp{C-c a a}
@tab Day/week agenda — deadlines, scheduled items (all files)
@item @samp{C-c a E}
@tab ★ Global dashboard (9 blocks) — spans all clients; pre-focused to active client when set; use @samp{/} to widen or refocus
@item @samp{C-c a t}
@tab All TODO items across all agenda files
@item @samp{C-c a m TAGNAME}
@tab Match by tag — e.g. @samp{RISK}, @samp{COMMITMENT}, @samp{DELEGATED}, @samp{BLOCKER}
@item @samp{C-c a s}
@tab Full-text search across all agenda files
@end multitable

@samp{C-c a E} is a first-class Org agenda command (so it exports, filters with @samp{/},
refreshes with @samp{r}, etc.). It spans @strong{all} client files; when an active client is
set the view opens pre-focused to it via @samp{org-agenda-tag-filter-preset} — the
@samp{CATEGORY} column shows each entry's client. Use @samp{/} to widen, refocus, or clear
the filter; there is no separate focus command. New clients work the moment
@samp{org-fractional-cto-new-client} scaffolds them — no per-client agenda config to
maintain. Blocks, in order: 7-day agenda → Delegated (WAITING) → Blockers → Open
Actions → Commitments → Active Risks → Open Security Findings → Open Tech Debt →
Scope Changes. @samp{M-x org-fractional-cto-switch-client} switches client and opens
it.

