@node How AI skills associate with an Org work item
@subsection How AI skills associate with an Org work item

There is no automatic binding between an Org heading and a skill — the link is
deliberate and manual, and that is the point. The flow is always:

@enumerate
@item
@strong{Pick the work item in Org} — an ADR you're about to write (@samp{ea}), a tech
spike (@samp{ek}), a discovery session (@samp{ed}), a security review (@samp{ex}).
@item
@strong{Open the client's code repo} in your AI tool (Claude Code, etc.) and load
its @samp{CONTEXT.md} so the agent has the domain vocabulary.
@item
@strong{Run the matching skill} in that repo's AI session (tables below).
@item
@strong{Capture the outcome} back into Org with the relevant @samp{e} key.
@end enumerate

So Org tells you @emph{what} and @emph{why}; the skill helps you @emph{do} it; Org records the
@emph{outcome}. The skills live in your code repositories, never in @samp{org-files}.

