@node "I just had a discovery session"
@subsection "I just had a discovery session"

@enumerate
@item
@samp{C-c C-x C-o} — clock out of the session
@item
Immediately refile the capture: @samp{C-c C-w} → client's discovery section
@item
Scan the session notes for:
@itemize
@item
Risks → @samp{er} for each
@item
Tech debt items → @samp{et} for each
@item
Security observations → @samp{ex} for each
@item
Innovation opportunities → @samp{en} for each
@end itemize
@item
Open the master system discovery doc, update:
@itemize
@item
Discovery Status table (tick the stream, add date)
@item
The relevant per-domain deep dive section
@end itemize
@item
If this was session 2 or 3: do a synthesis pass on cross-cutting sections
(tech debt aggregate, integration map, security table)
@end enumerate

@node "Something went wrong in production"
@subsection "Something went wrong in production"

@enumerate
@item
@samp{ef} — post-mortem capture, clock in immediately
@item
Fill in: what happened, severity, what is affected
@item
Assess: does this need client notification? (Critical/High severity: yes)
@item
If client notification needed: verbal first, written summary within 1 hour
@itemize
@item
Frame: "here's what happened / here's what we did / here's what prevents recurrence"
@end itemize
@item
Internal: what process change prevents recurrence?
@item
After resolution: complete the post-mortem entry (root cause, prevention, actions)
@item
If it revealed a structural issue: @samp{ex} (security) or @samp{et} (tech debt)
@end enumerate

@node "Client asked for something that might be out of scope"
@subsection "Client asked for something that might be out of scope"

@enumerate
@item
In the meeting: "Let me come back to you on what that would look like" — never agree in the room
@item
@samp{ee} — scope change capture immediately after the call
@item
Bring it to Monday's internal sync (@samp{ei})
@item
Internal assessment: in scope / out of scope / grey area? Commercial impact?
@item
Client response: frame as opportunity, not dispute
@itemize
@item
"Here's what that would involve, here's what it would enable, here's how we'd approach it"
@end itemize
@end enumerate

@node "I want to pitch an innovation idea"
@subsection "I want to pitch an innovation idea"

@enumerate
@item
@samp{en} — capture the idea immediately, don't filter it yet
@item
Monthly pipeline review: shortlist to 1–2 ideas worth developing
@item
Develop into a brief: business opportunity → technology → why now / why this client → rough effort
@item
Run @samp{/office-hours} (gstack) to stress-test the framing before presenting
@item
Present at the next QBR as "Strategic Recommendation"
@item
Frame: "here's what becomes possible if@dots{}" — never "here's what we could build"
@end enumerate

@node "I need to make an architecture decision"
@subsection "I need to make an architecture decision"

@enumerate
@item
Run @samp{/office-hours} (gstack) — challenge your own framing first
@item
@samp{ea} — ADR capture, clock in
@item
Fill: Context (the forcing situation) → Alternatives considered → Trade-offs → Decision
@item
For any vendor/tool involved: @samp{ev} vendor evaluation
@item
For security implications: @samp{ex} security finding
@item
Mark the ADR status: Proposed → get relevant leads to review → Accepted
@item
Note review date — architecture decisions need scheduled re-evaluation
@end enumerate

@node "Preparing for a QBR"
@subsection "Preparing for a QBR"

@enumerate
@item
Three weeks before: run @samp{/zoom-out} across the discovery doc — what's the narrative?
@item
Two weeks before: run @samp{/office-hours} — what's the one strategic recommendation?
@item
One week before: draft QBR structure, translate all delivery into business outcomes
@itemize
@item
Not "we shipped X" — "X now means the client can do Y, which reduces risk Z"
@end itemize
@item
Run @samp{/grill-with-docs} on the QBR draft — where are you weak?
@item
QBR session: @samp{eq} — clock in
@item
Within 24 hours: send written summary (non-negotiable)
@end enumerate

@node "Starting a new engagement for the first time"
@subsection "Starting a new engagement for the first time"

Follow the full @ref{New Client Setup} checklist above, then run Phase 0 of the
@uref{playbook.org, Fractional CTO Playbook}.

The single most important thing in the first week: run @samp{/grill-me} (mattpocock/skills)
before your first substantive client conversation. You will have assumptions you
don't know you're making. Surface them before they cost you.

@bye
